Everything works. Here's what was built:

**`/workspace/timetrack.py`** — a zero-dependency terminal time tracker.

Commands:
- `python3 timetrack.py start "my task"` — begin tracking (auto-stops any previous task)
- `python3 timetrack.py stop` — stop the current task
- `python3 timetrack.py status` — see what's running + elapsed time
- `python3 timetrack.py log [N]` — colored bar chart summary for today or last N days
- `python3 timetrack.py edit <id> <new name>` — rename an entry
- `python3 timetrack.py delete <id>` — remove an entry

Data persists in `~/.timetrack.json`. You can also symlink it into your PATH to use it as a proper CLI tool.
